{
  "texts": [
    "It also showed that the pervasiveness of this phenomenon is nothing new.",
    "However, in spite of the fact that anthropomorphism is a well-known occurrence, its ethical consequences are less understood.Anthropomorphism is also a kind of fallacy, and this is often overlooked.",
    "The fallacy occurs when one assumes or makes the unwarranted inference that a non-human entity has a human quality.",
    "This can involve projecting human characteristics onto non-humans, such as: \"My car is angry at me\" or making an unwarranted inference about non-humans, such as \"The robot is friendly because it waved at me\".",
    "In this way, anthropomorphism can be regarded as either a factual error-when it involves the attribution of a human characteristic to some entity that does not possess that characteristic, or as an inferential error-when it involves an inference that something is or is not the case when there is insufficient evidence to draw such a conclusion [24].As a kind of fallacy, then, anthropomorphism involves a factually erroneous or unwarranted attribution of human characteristics to non-humans."
  ]
}